<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#123#000055#        43#">Va. Code Ann. § 55-43</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_55-43"/><heading><desig>§ 55-43.</desig><title>Appointment of attorney in fact by married women; effect of writing executed by such attorney</title></heading><bodyText><p>A married woman, whether a resident of this Commonwealth or not, may, by power of attorney duly executed and acknowledged as prescribed in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-113"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -113">§ 55-113<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#       113#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 55-114"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 55 -114">§ 55-114<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000055#       114#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, appoint an attorney-in-fact to execute and acknowledge, for her and in her name, any deed or other writing which she might execute. Every deed or other writing so executed by such attorney-in-fact in pursuance of such power of attorney while the same remains in force shall be valid and effectual, in all respects, to convey the interest and title of such married woman in and to any real estate thereby conveyed or otherwise transferred.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1919, § 5215; 1940, p. 53; <citation normalizedCite="1990 VA CH 831"><content><span normalizedCite="1990 Va. Ch. 831">1990, c. 831<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1990#000831#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PTT0-004G-K3BD-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 55.</desig><title>PROPERTY AND CONVEYANCES</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 3.</desig><title>PROPERTY RIGHTS OF MARRIED WOMEN</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Real Property Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QUUyRTcxRURBNEY2NEE2MDk3QzBCNzRDOEY0NTZDQzk7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Natural Persons</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6M0EzQzNFMjkwQzkwNDZGNzlDREFFNkQyM0NCMUE1REY7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6RURDNjE0NDUzN0QxNDE4OTg0OERFMzU4MzFCNUU1NUI</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Powers of Attorney</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QjNFQzY1NzBFNEMxNDhGOEExRTk3RkVERTBFOUQwOTA7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6RURDNjE0NDUzN0QxNDE4OTg0OERFMzU4MzFCNUU1NUI</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem></classification><classificationGroup classificationScheme="i